{"message": "## Summary

The issue was that the `onResponse` callback provided in the REST helper config was not being called when using `JSONResponse` helper alongside `REST`.

### Root Cause

In `JSONResponse._beforeSuite()` (line 76-78 of `lib/helper/JSONResponse.js`), the code was directly replacing `REST.config.onResponse` with JSONResponse's own callback:

```js
this.helpers[this.options.requestHelper].config.onResponse = response => {
    this.response = response
}
```

This **overwrote** the user's `onResponse` callback, so it never got called.

### Fix

Modified `JSONResponse._beforeSuite()` in `/workspace/CodeceptJS/lib/helper/JSONResponse.js` to preserve any existing `onResponse` callback by chaining it:

```js
const existingOnResponse = this.helpers[this.options.requestHelper].config.onResponse
this.helpers[this.options.requestHelper].config.onResponse = response => {
    if (existingOnResponse) {
        existingOnResponse(response)
    }
    this.response = response
}
```

Now both the user's `onResponse` callback and JSONResponse's internal callback are called when a response is received. The `onRequest` callback was not affected because JSONResponse doesn't override it.", "summary": "Fixed JSONResponse to chain onResponse callbacks instead of overwriting"}
